data.name: Tofu Scramble

ingredients.name: chopped vegetables (e.g., bell peppers, spinach, tomatoes)

data.quickTastyDescription: A flavorful and protein-packed alternative to scrambled eggs, perfect for breakfast or brunch!
detailedCookingInstructions: Drain and press the tofu to remove excess moisture, then crumble it into a bowl.
In a non-stick skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add the crumbled tofu to the skillet and cook for about 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle in the turmeric, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper, stirring to combine.
Add the chopped vegetables and cook for an additional 3-5 minutes until the veggies are tender and the tofu is heated through.
If using, stir in the nutritional yeast for a cheesy flavor.
Serve warm, optionally with toast or avocado on the side.
data.modifiersForBase: Add your favorite vegetables for extra flavor and nutrition.
